Having learned from his friends that his recall was merely a question of time, he had returned in November, 58, to Dyrrachium, where he waited and watched the progress of eventa. He sailed for Brun- disium as it chanced on the very day that the people authorized his return, and reached Italy on the 5th of August, after an absence of about sixteen months. At , Brundisium his daughter Tullia met him,-the 5th ol August happened to be her birthday,-and here on the - 8th hc learned finally that his bauishment was at an end. His return to Rome was a triumphal march.
